The Vice President, Kamala Harris, spoke at Howard University about the importance of fighting for women's rights and reproductive freedom. She criticized the recent attacks on abortion rights and highlighted the national agenda behind these attacks. Harris emphasized the need for empathy and understanding in leadership and called on the audience to stand up and fight for their beliefs. She also addressed other issues such as voting rights, gun violence, and LGBTQ+ rights. Harris urged the audience to take a stand and protect the ideals of democracy.